  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A decision just rendered by City\nAttorney Geraghty upon the ordi.\nnance to name a depository for city\nfunds in the city treasurer's hands\nwill put an end to the attempt upon\nthe part of certain corporate in\nterests in the city and their repre-\nsentative in the council, Hon. Jack\nSnyder, to secure control of an in\ncome from the peoples money.\n\n\nAttorney Geraghty says for the\ncity council to designate a deposit\ntory for public funds would be in\ncontravention of the city charter.\nThe charter holds the city treasurer\nresponsible for all public money\nand he is under bond to insure the\ncity. If the city directs where\nfunds shall be kept, it relieves him"
    }
